    "Because this distribution depends on the task but is independent of the input distribution, we shall write p(y, x, ρ) = p(y|x, ρ)p(x)p(ρ).",
    "Please note that the distribution p(ρ) is not uniform.",
    "In practice, LLMs implement the distribution p(y|x, ρ), hence we can define the average probability that an LLM predicts the class y under different variants of the same prompt as",
    "which is different from the class distribution predicted by classifiers for a fixed x.",
    "Similarly to p(x), p(ρ) is unknown; therefore, we can approximate Equation 1 using a sampler S (Barber, 2012) over Q semantically equivalent prompts ρ 1,."
